events.text: Oh my gosh, seeing you after today is everything.
Hmm, looks like you ate the lettuce I laid out.
Hmm, looks like you ate the peaches I laid out.
Hmm, looks like you ate the tomatoes I laid out.

events.choice: I want to see you grow.

events.text: I love you, but Tootroots are supposed to sprout…
Do you not have what you need here?
But…you have food, water, and light.

events.question: Plus, you’re acting normally, so the temperature should also be fine…

events.text: It could be the change in environment that’s causing the delay…
There’s no rush, [tootroot], you sprout whenever you’re comfortable!
But I’m already so attached, [tootroot], what am I going to do without you?
Aw man, I’m going to miss you.
You’ll have to visit! I’ll always have fresh veggies for you!
One more scratch! Lemme itch those scutes for you.
Okay, [tootroot], I love you. The door’s open.

events.choice: Not that you have to sprout!

events.text: But don’t worry, [tootroot], you don’t have to sprout!
I love you just the way you are!

Let me get you some scratches!
Right between those scutes, you like that, right?

I wish we could stay like this, [tootroot].
It would be simpler, wouldn’t it?

Well, you make me happier, [tootroot].
I hope I make you happier.
[color=#ffed29](It’s a long shot, but maybe [tootroot] is back?)
I’m so glad you came back!
Let’s get you some more lettuce, and I’ll get a cool bath going too!
They grow up so fast…but I’m glad you’re back!
Come in, come in! I’ll get you more peaches, and I’ll get a cool bath going too.
You’re so leafy, I love the new cut!
You gotta come in! I’ll get you some more tomatoes, draw a cool bath, it’ll be great!
I’m so glad you’re doing well.
So, is this what we’re doing? You’ll pay visits in the afternoon and do your thing the rest of the day?
What do you do when you’re out there?
Wow, you make quite a trek every day, don’t you?
Matty, you can’t run off like that! It’s dangerous!
Tooty, did you make a friend?

Oh, hello!
My name is Meldan, and I watch over these kiddos.

My name is Lunette!
And this is my brother…
Sorry, his name is Matty! He’s a little shy.

events.question: [color=#ffed29](These names sound familiar…who talked about “Lunette” and “Matty”?)

events.text: [color=#ffed29](Did I hear about it from Miss Odiche? I feel like she’s always talking…)
Do you guys know Miss Odiche?
[color=#ffed29](Matty is hiding behind his sister…that’s not good.)
Friends might be strong. We work together.
Uh, sorry! I didn’t know you guys didn’t like her.
She says mean things about my mom.

That’s okay, we should probably get going, though.
Say goodbye!
Well, I’m glad I didn’t scare you off, too.
For that, I’ll give you extra pets and snacks!
[color=#ffed29](Maybe Herb? He’s got a ton of siblings, so maybe through them?)
Do you guys know someone named Herwin?
We don’t know anyone named Herwin.
Well, I’m glad I didn’t scare you off, too.
For that, I’ll give you extra pets and snacks!

......
Well! I think it’s time for us to go, right, kids?
Well, I’m glad I didn’t scare you off, too.
For that, I’ll give you extra pets and snacks!
[color=#ffed29](I’m pretty sure...these are the Avidine children!)
[color=#ffed29](Let’s see if me knowing their dad can get Matty to open up a little.)
Do you go to Dad’s job during the day?
I do! And he says a lot of good things about you guys.

events.question: [color=#ffed29](What did Mister Avidine say about Matty?)
[color=#ffed29](What did Mister Avidine say about Matty?)

events.choice: That you're his joy and delight.

events.text: That you’re endlessly joyful, and a delight to all that meet you!

events.question: And me??? What does Dad say about me???

events.text: That you are a beautiful young lady, who does things very gracefully!

Matty, that’s not nice!  
Your sister is beautiful and ladylike!

Lunette bumps into things all the time!
And FARTS. She’s not like mom.
But I’m trying to be more like her! She’s the coolest and prettiest mom in the world!
Well, I think you’re a very pretty lady as you are.
Mom and Dad say that, too. But I can do better!
You’re doing great as you are, Lunette.
Thanks, Meldan! I try to try hard.
And I know one more thing!
What! What else does Dad say?
[color=#ffed29](Oh no! I ran out of time…)
I don’t think you actually know our dad…
Well, I’m glad I didn’t scare you off, too.
For that, I’ll give you extra pets and snacks!
He says that you’re very good at the piano, and that you’re very very smart.
he likes talking to you more than most adults!
Wow! Not even Rondeau got the uncle title this quickly.
Uncle Orven isn’t as big as Uncle Rondeau, so he was less scary.
[color=#ffed29](THIS KID IS HEAVY! HOW LONG CAN I KEEP THIS UP???)

[i]pant
[shake rate=20.0 level=5 connected=1]I don’t know...
[i]pant
[shake rate=20.0 level=5 connected=1]...about that???
Next time we see Tooty, can we see you, Uncle Orven?

Whenever you guys are free, I’ll be here with Tooty.
I call her, [tootroot]!

You see these plants on her face?
Because they’re heart shaped and not circles, you know she’s a girl!
Uncle Orven knows so much about Tooty!

Is it okay if we keep calling her Tooty?
Can she have two names?
Sure! People call me different things.
My Gramma calls me Orven, my friend Herb calls me Orvo, and you guys call me Uncle Orven!
Ooh! Matty, you can call him, "Uncle Orvo," and I’ll call him, "Uncle Orven"!
[i]Haha![/i] Come on, guys, we gotta head back.
You should come over sometime, Uncle Orven!
[color=#ffed29](I could go to Mister Avidine’s mansion???)
We should probably run this by your parents first, right?
We’ll ask Mr. and Mrs. Avidine, and if they approve, we’ll get back to you.
Maybe Mister Avidine can tell me at work?
I’ll probably be the one reaching out.
Oh, okay, either way is fine with me!

Thanks, buddy. This was great.
I see why you don’t wanna be stuck in a house.
There are a lot of cool people out here.
Alright, lots of scute scratches and snacks before I go back home.

Okay, I actually have to go back home.
I’ll see you soon, stay safe!
[color=#ffed29](As much as I’d love to, I’m not sure if my boss would be super happy about me showing up at his house.)
We should probably ask your mom and dad, right?
If they say yes, will you come?
[color=#ffed29](I don’t want to overstep with Meldan either…)
[i]Haha[/i], don’t worry, if it’s okay with their parents, you’re in the clear.
Alright! You check with your parents, okay?

Thanks, buddy. This was great.
I see why you don’t wanna be stuck in a house.
There are a lot of cool people out here.
Alright, lots of scute scratches and snacks before I go back home.

Okay, I actually have to go back home.
I’ll see you soon, stay safe!
That you’re what makes him strong!
[color=#ffed29](Oh no! I ran out of time…)
I don’t think you actually know our dad…
Well, I’m glad I didn’t scare you off, too.
For that, I’ll give you extra pets and snacks!
He says you guys are VERY special!
Mom says that we’re very special and very loved!
Mister Avidine says that more than anything, he’s proud to be your dad.

Well, you can tell Dad that we love him!
And we’re proud to be his kids!
[i]Haha,[/i] I think you guys can probably do that tonight, right?
Sometimes Dad goes out at night, so I thought maybe he’d be at work?
[color=#ffed29](He did pull an all nighter for [b]Remedium[/b], but Mr. Gungand said he went back home.)
That was just for last night, I think he might be waiting for you guys at home!

Okay!
Matty, Dad’s gonna be home tonight!
Do you think he’ll play games with us?

Uh! I think he might be a little tired.
He worked really hard these past couple days…

…...
Maybe we can make him something to feel better?
I’ll draw me and dad, and you can draw you and mom.
Let’s go, Meldan! We have to get this ready for dad!
Thank you for the idea, Mr. Orven!

Thanks, buddy. This was great.
I see why you don’t wanna be stuck in a house. There are a lot of cool people out here.
Alright, lots of scute scratches and snacks before I go back home.

Okay, I actually have to go back home.
I’ll see you soon, stay safe!

events.choice: I can’t remember why these names are familiar.

events.text:
[color=#ffed29](I can’t remember. Let’s not be weird, Matty is already shy.)
Did you know I was shy as a kid, too…
but you know what’s exciting?
No, we’re not? I just met you!
My name is Orven, and I’m friends with Tooty!
I do! And I was the one that gave her the lettuce she’s sprouting!
I do! And I was the one that gave her the peaches she’s sprouting!
I do! And I was the one that gave her the tomatoes she’s sprouting!
So since we’re both friends with Tooty, I think we can be friends?
Well…I have a fun fact about Tooty!
Not true! Meldan said Tooty is a boy!
i guessed, is it really a girl?
yeah…you can tell by if the plants on their temples are clefted or not.
Meldan, did you lie to us???

events.choice: You gotta tell them the truth.

events.text: you gotta be the example and come clean.
me neither, i can’t help you.

Sorry, sorry! I didn’t lie. I swear!
I didn’t know, but I shouldn’t have made it up. I’m sorry.
I’m sorry, Tooty, you’re a lovely young lady.
It’s hard to tell a tootroot’s age, but she’s definitely not a baby!
I think Orven knows a lot more about tootroots than you do, Meldan.

Definitely.
Oh! It’s getting late, looks like we have to say goodbye to our new friend and Tooty!
Bye, guys! Next time you see Tooty, she might be fully bloomed!
It’s late for me, too. I gotta call my Gramma, [tootroot].
I know they call you Tooty, but I think I can keep calling you [tootroot], right?
This was nice! Good to know you’re making a lot of people happy.
Alright! A couple of scute scratches and a snack!
I’ll see you soon, stay safe!
